[SN]TITLE[SN]
Borders General Hospital affected by flu outbreak

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A flu outbreak has closed part of a ward at Borders General Hospital.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Three bays of Ward 10, which is part of the Medicine for the Elderly Department, are affected.
NHS Borders said the infection had been confirmed as the Influenza A strain. It is "discouraging" routine visits to the unit.
It has also asked anyone with symptoms of flu not to visit the BGH at all and has urged anyone with underlying conditions to get a flu vaccination.
